00:11:56.861 --> 00:11:59.489 line:90% position:50% align:center
“On the first day of the Unleavened Bread,

00:11:59.489 --> 00:12:02.409 line:90% position:50% align:center
“the disciples came to Jesus, saying:

00:12:02.409 --> 00:12:06.246 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘Where do you want us to prepare
for you to eat the Passover?’

00:12:06.246 --> 00:12:10.542 line:90% position:50% align:center
“He said: ‘Go into the city to So-and-so

00:12:10.542 --> 00:12:13.545 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘and say to him, “The Teacher says:

00:12:13.545 --> 00:12:15.714 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘“‘My appointed time is near;

00:12:15.714 --> 00:12:18.091 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘“‘I will celebrate the Passover

00:12:18.091 --> 00:12:19.926 line:90% position:50% align:center
with my disciples at your home.’”’

00:12:20.760 --> 00:12:23.888 line:90% position:50% align:center
“So the disciples did
as Jesus instructed them

00:12:23.888 --> 00:12:25.890 line:90% position:50% align:center
and prepared for the Passover.”

00:12:33.189 --> 00:12:36.276 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Now on the first day
of the Unleavened Bread,

00:12:36.276 --> 00:12:40.697 line:90% position:50% align:center
“when they customarily
offered up the Passover sacrifice,

00:12:40.697 --> 00:12:43.617 line:90% position:50% align:center
“his disciples said to him:

00:12:43.617 --> 00:12:47.329 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘Where do you want us to go
and prepare for you to eat the Passover?’

00:12:47.329 --> 00:12:52.292 line:90% position:50% align:center
“With that he sent two
of his disciples and said to them:

00:12:52.292 --> 00:12:54.336 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘Go into the city,

00:12:54.336 --> 00:12:58.131 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘and a man carrying
an earthenware water jar will meet you.

00:12:58.131 --> 00:13:01.676 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘Follow him, and wherever he goes inside,

00:13:01.676 --> 00:13:04.137 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘say to the master of the house,

00:13:04.137 --> 00:13:07.182 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘“The Teacher says: ‘Where is the guest room

00:13:07.182 --> 00:13:10.727 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘“where I may eat
the Passover with my disciples?’

00:13:10.727 --> 00:13:15.190 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘And he will show you
a large upper room, furnished and ready.

00:13:15.190 --> 00:13:17.692 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Prepare it for us there.’

00:13:17.692 --> 00:13:19.944 line:90% position:50% align:center
“So the disciples went out,

00:13:19.944 --> 00:13:24.491 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and they entered the city
and found it just as he said to them,

00:13:24.491 --> 00:13:27.118 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and they prepared for the Passover.

00:13:34.584 --> 00:13:37.212 line:90% position:50% align:center
“The day
of the Unleavened Bread now arrived,

00:13:37.212 --> 00:13:41.216 line:90% position:50% align:center
“on which
the Passover sacrifice must be offered;

00:13:41.216 --> 00:13:44.844 line:90% position:50% align:center
“so Jesus sent Peter and John, saying:

00:13:44.844 --> 00:13:48.473 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘Go and get
the Passover ready for us to eat.’

00:13:48.473 --> 00:13:52.519 line:90% position:50% align:center
“They said to him:
‘Where do you want us to get it ready?’

00:13:52.519 --> 00:13:56.856 line:90% position:50% align:center
“He said to them: ‘Look!
When you enter into the city,

00:13:56.856 --> 00:14:01.319 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘a man carrying
an earthenware water jar will meet you.

00:14:01.319 --> 00:14:03.947 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘Follow him into the house that he enters.

00:14:03.947 --> 00:14:06.574 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘And say to the landlord of the house,

00:14:06.574 --> 00:14:10.495 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘“The Teacher says to you:
‘Where is the guest room

00:14:10.495 --> 00:14:14.666 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘where I may eat the Passover
with my disciples?’”

00:14:14.666 --> 00:14:18.420 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘And that man will show you a large,
furnished upper room.

00:14:18.420 --> 00:14:20.964 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Get it ready there.’

00:14:20.964 --> 00:14:24.634 line:90% position:50% align:center
“So they left and found it
just as he had told them,

00:14:24.634 --> 00:14:26.845 line:90% position:50% align:center
and they prepared for the Passover.”

00:14:33.810 --> 00:14:37.605 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Now because he knew
before the festival of the Passover

00:14:37.605 --> 00:14:42.068 line:90% position:50% align:center
“that his hour had come for him
to leave this world and go to the Father,

00:14:42.068 --> 00:14:45.947 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Jesus, having loved his own
who were in the world,

00:14:45.947 --> 00:14:48.533 line:90% position:50% align:center
“loved them to the end.

00:14:48.533 --> 00:14:50.952 line:90% position:50% align:center
“The evening meal was going on,

00:14:50.952 --> 00:14:55.248 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and the Devil had already put it
into the heart of Judas Iscariot,

00:14:55.248 --> 00:14:58.293 line:90% position:50% align:center
“the son of Simon, to betray him.

00:14:58.293 --> 00:15:01.254 line:90% position:50% align:center
“So Jesus, knowing that the Father

00:15:01.254 --> 00:15:03.715 line:90% position:50% align:center
“had given all things into his hands

00:15:03.715 --> 00:15:07.343 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and that he came from God
and was going to God,

00:15:07.343 --> 00:15:12.724 line:90% position:50% align:center
“got up from the evening meal
and laid aside his outer garments.

00:15:12.724 --> 00:15:17.228 line:90% position:50% align:center
“And taking a towel,
he wrapped it around his waist.

00:15:17.228 --> 00:15:20.690 line:90% position:50% align:center
“After that he put water into a basin

00:15:20.690 --> 00:15:24.068 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and started
to wash the feet of the disciples

00:15:24.068 --> 00:15:28.198 line:90% position:50% align:center
and to dry them off with the towel
that was wrapped around him.”

00:15:35.121 --> 00:15:37.540 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Do not let your hearts be troubled.

00:15:37.540 --> 00:15:40.084 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Exercise faith in God;

00:15:40.084 --> 00:15:43.213 line:90% position:50% align:center
“exercise faith also in me.

00:15:43.213 --> 00:15:47.342 line:90% position:50% align:center
“In the house of my Father
are many dwelling places.

00:15:47.342 --> 00:15:50.178 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Otherwise, I would have told you,

00:15:50.178 --> 00:15:53.932 line:90% position:50% align:center
“for I am going my way
to prepare a place for you.

00:15:53.932 --> 00:15:58.186 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Also, if I go my way
and prepare a place for you,

00:15:58.186 --> 00:16:02.482 line:90% position:50% align:center
“I will come again
and will receive you home to myself,

00:16:02.482 --> 00:16:06.194 line:90% position:50% align:center
so that where I am you also may be.”

00:16:08.279 --> 00:16:10.573 line:90% position:50% align:center
Those were significant passages

00:16:10.573 --> 00:16:13.910 line:90% position:50% align:center
leading up to the greatest act of love

00:16:13.910 --> 00:16:16.162 line:90% position:50% align:center
of all time.

00:16:16.162 --> 00:16:20.124 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah and Jesus cooperated together

00:16:20.124 --> 00:16:22.836 line:90% position:50% align:center
to undo the horrible results

00:16:22.836 --> 00:16:26.923 line:90% position:50% align:center
that came from the actions
of Satan, Adam, and Eve.

00:16:26.923 --> 00:16:30.718 line:90% position:50% align:center
Whether of the anointed or the other sheep,

00:16:30.718 --> 00:16:32.720 line:90% position:50% align:center
we look forward to the future

00:16:32.720 --> 00:16:36.099 line:90% position:50% align:center
when we will always acknowledge the role

00:16:36.099 --> 00:16:38.142 line:90% position:50% align:center
that both Jehovah and Jesus played

00:16:38.142 --> 00:16:41.980 line:90% position:50% align:center
in rescuing us from sin and death.

00:16:41.980 --> 00:16:45.984 line:90% position:50% align:center
We pray that all of you
will enjoy your evening

00:16:45.984 --> 00:16:48.903 line:90% position:50% align:center
during the Memorial of Jesus’ death.

